of Terrorism/Piracy or Security Incidents, please refer to Section 4‘Emergency Procedures’ of the Emergency Contingency and Planning Manual.2) CSO will contact the vessel after about 10 minutes and request to speak to Master, pretending to discuss routine matters.3) While speaking to Master, CSO will enquire if everything is in order and if possible, Master may be requested to speak in alanguage other than English.4) CSO will then assess the situation and update Managing Director and other members of the emergency team.5) Notify the owners, classification society, flag authority, H&M underwriters and/or P&I club.6) Contact the local authorities in order to deal with the situation.7.5.11ACTION TO BE TAKEN IF VESSEL HAS BEEN ATTACKED OR HIJACKEDCompany security officer (CSO) is responsible for keeping a track of all company operated vessels trading in the “high security risk”areas.All company operated vessels are polled / tracked on immediately:1) CSO to inform managing
